  | rem i 3 == 0 = if i == 0 && (k /= 0) then (c k) else (h j)
  | otherwise = 0
  where i = sum ‚ñà@dots{}
}

The other functionality @code{M-x haskell-hide-toggle-all} also
works only for indentation and it collapses all toplevel functions.

So a file that looks like this:

@example
